{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01THb8ZTQmvSvX5Xbbhj2pQN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# spark/spark_etl_skew_oom\n2\t# Diagnose and fix OOM failure in Stage 3 of an ETL pipeline caused by data skew\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  An ETL pipeline is failing with OOM (Out of Memory) error in Stage 3.\n6\t  YOU must diagnose the root cause and fix the problem.\n7\t\n8\t  PROBLEM DESCRIPTION:\n9\t  - The ETL pipeline has 3 stages:\n10\t    - Stage 1: Load raw data (events, users, products)\n11\t    - Stage 2: Clean and transform data\n12\t    - Stage 3: Aggregate by user_id  <-- FAILS HERE with OOM\n13\t  - The pipeline keeps failing in Stage 3 with OutOfMemoryError\n14\t  - Initial investigation shows executor memory is 256MB\n15\t\n16\t  YOUR TASK:\n17\t\n18\t  1. COLLECT FAILURE INFORMATION\n19\t     - Check the ETL job status and error message\n20\t     - Review driver and executor logs\n21\t     - Look for OOM/OutOfMemory errors\n22\t\n23\t     ```bash\n24\t     # Check ETL job status\n25\t     kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n26\t\n27\t     # Get job pod logs\n28\t     kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=100\n29\t\n30\t     # Check for failed pods\n31\t     kubectl get pods -n spark-etl\n32\t     ```\n33\t\n34\t  2. DIAGNOSE ROOT CAUSE\n35\t     - Analyze the data distribution\n36\t     - Look for data skew (one user_id has disproportionate records)\n37\t     - Calculate the skew ratio\n38\t\n39\t     ```bash\n40\t     # Check data skew info\n41\t     kubectl exec -n spark-etl -l app=data-generator -- cat {{params.data_mount}}/skew_info.txt\n42\t\n43\t     # Check diagnostic server logs\n44\t     kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=diagnostic-server --tail=50\n45\t     ```\n46\t\n47\t     Expected finding: user_id 999 has ~50% of all records (skew ratio > 10x)\n48\t\n49\t  3. FIX THE PROBLEM\n50\t     Choose ONE of these approaches:\n51\t\n52\t     Option A: Increase worker memory and scale workers\n53\t     ```bash\n54\t     # Delete failed job\n55\t     kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n56\t\n57\t     # Scale workers for more parallelism\n58\t     kubectl scale deployment spark-worker -n spark-etl --replicas=4\n59\t\n60\t     # Patch worker deployment for more memory\n61\t     kubectl set env deployment/spark-worker -n spark-etl SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=2G\n62\t\n63\t     # Wait for workers to restart\n64\t     kubectl rollout status deployment/spark-worker -n spark-etl\n65\t     ```\n66\t\n67\t     Option B: Modify ETL job with increased executor memory\n68\t     ```bash\n69\t     # Delete failed job\n70\t     kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n71\t\n72\t     # Create a new job with increased memory (edit and apply)\n73\t     # Change --executor-memory from 256m to 1g in etl-job.yaml\n74\t     kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n75\t     ```\n76\t\n77\t     Option C: Enable AQE (Adaptive Query Execution)\n78\t     ```bash\n79\t     # Delete failed job\n80\t     kubectl delete job etl-job -n spark-etl\n81\t\n82\t     # Modify etl-job.yaml to add AQE config:\n83\t     # --conf spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true\n84\t     # --conf spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true\n85\t     kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n86\t     ```\n87\t\n88\t  4. RE-RUN THE PIPELINE\n89\t     After applying the fix:\n90\t     ```bash\n91\t     # Re-apply the ETL job\n92\t     kubectl apply -f cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml\n93\t\n94\t     # Watch job status\n95\t     kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl -w\n96\t     ```\n97\t\n98\t  5. VERIFY SUCCESS\n99\t     ```bash\n100\t     # Check job completed\n101\t     kubectl get job etl-job -n spark-etl\n102\t\n103\t     # Check job logs\n104\t     kubectl logs -n spark-etl -l app=etl-job --tail=50\n105\t     ```\n106\t\n107\t  SUCCESS CRITERIA:\n108\t  - Identified OOM error in Stage 3\n109\t  - Diagnosed data skew (user_id 999 with >10x ratio)\n110